== English ==
=== Etymology ===
From the Greek ''[[demagogos]]'' "leader" from ''[[demos]]'' "people" + ''[[agogos]]'' "leader"

=== Noun ===
'''demagogue''' ''or'' '''demagog'''
# an [[orator]] or leader who gains favor by exciting the [[passion]]s and [[prejudice]]s of the audience
# (ancient) a leader of the people

=== Verb ===
# to speak or act in the manner of a demagogue
:: '''[[nota bene|n.b.]]''' ''The use of '''demagogue''' as a verb is widely regarded as inappropriate in the linguistic community.  The form is, however, in common usage.''

=== Adjective ===
'''demogogic'''
# [[characteristic]] of a demagogue